<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26268e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26268e">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26268e"> 268(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> juger</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Institutions of the Private Law. Property in land. Patricians.]</font>&mdash;Varro and Pliny relate that to each <i>paterfamilias</i> among his followers <font color="green">[Romulus]</font> assigned a homestead (<i>heredium</i>) of two <mark>jugera</mark>, equal to about an acre and a quarter. These <i>heredia</i> were to be held <font color="green">[but inalienable]</font> by him and his heirs for ever <font color="green">[and]</font> to none did the king give more. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 531</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
